The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Hughes bottomline rises

 New Delhi, Jan. 19 (PTI): Hughes Software Systems has posted a 15.48 per cent year-on-year increase in net profit in the third quarter ended December 2004.

 The total income of the company was up 25 per cent at Rs 123.5 crore compared with the year-ago period. On consolidated basis, the group?s net profit increased 18 per cent during the quarter to Rs 27.7 crore on an income of Rs 125.5 crore. ?It has been yet another quarter of predictable steady growth. We continue to strengthen and broaden our customer relationships,? president and managing director Arun Kumar said.

 In the fourth quarter, Hughes has forecast a sales growth of 4.5-5 per cent on a quarter-on-quarter basis and a profit-after-tax margin of 21.5-22 per cent.

 Hughes added nine clients ? six in products and three in services ? during the quarter.

 The BPO business of the company also got its second client. 




